You are given a list of outcomes from a dialogue. (1) Identify distinct **intentions** (high-level goals or purposes) that these outcomes serve. (2) Assign each outcome to exactly one intention.

Output JSON only:
{
  "intentions": [
    {"intention_id": "I1", "intention": "short label"},
    {"intention_id": "I2", "intention": "another label"}
  ],
  "outcome_to_intention": [{"outcome_id": "outcome_1", "intention_id": "I1"}, ...]
}
- Every outcome_id appears exactly once in outcome_to_intention. Use intention_id from the intentions list.

Outcomes:
[
  {
    "outcome_id": "outcome_1",
    "description": "One-day NYC itinerary for the parents (8am–8pm) optimized for a laidback pace (low walking/crowds) with some famous landmarks and NYC-only cultural food"
  },
  {
    "outcome_id": "outcome_2",
    "description": "Simplified one-sheet itinerary overview with high-priority vs optional markings"
  },
  {
    "outcome_id": "outcome_3",
    "description": "Itinerary annotated with reservations/tickets requirements and how far in advance to book"
  },
  {
    "outcome_id": "outcome_4",
    "description": "Itinerary annotated with commute time estimates and whether subway is needed between stops"
  },
  {
    "outcome_id": "outcome_5",
    "description": "Updated itinerary with quieter hole-in-the-wall restaurant swaps and added lunch options (avoiding trendy/crowded spots), plus built-in ~30-minute rest breaks"
  }
]

List intentions and assign each outcome to one. JSON only.

